            "type": "text",
            "text": "Deployment in the LLMOps Lifecycle"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Deploying an LLM-based application involves more components than a traditional ML serving endpoint. The system must route traffic, enforce guardrails, select the right model for each request, retrieve relevant context, and log everything for quality monitoring \u2014 all in a single request path that must return within seconds. Understanding the topology before choosing tools prevents expensive rearchitecting later."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "LLMOps deployment topology: client \u2192 gateway/router \u2192 guardrails \u2192 LLM API (control + canary) \u2192 RAG retriever; observability, async eval, and cost tracker on the side; versioned config store underneath"
        }
      },
