          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LLMOps deployment is a layered system: a gateway/router handles authentication, rate limiting, model selection, and canary splitting; guardrails filter inputs and outputs for safety and policy compliance; the LLM API serves streamed or blocking completions against a pinned model version; a RAG retriever augments responses with fresh context; and observability, async eval, and cost tracking run on the side without adding latency to the request path. Every dynamic parameter \u2014 model pin, prompt version, canary split \u2014 lives in a versioned config store and can be changed without redeployment. A pre-deployment checklist that gates on eval pass rate, cost estimate, and rollback readiness reduces the risk of shipping regressions to production."
          }
        ]
      }
